This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump during the "Take Our Daughters and Sons to Work Day" event at the White House. The President welcomed the children and praised their parents for their hard work in keeping the country safe and prosperous. He also emphasized the importance of staying away from drugs, alcohol, and smoking. The President highlighted the significance of the White House and encouraged the children to continue learning and dreaming. He expressed gratitude to the children for their support and thanked them for attending the event.